"Gamma Swap is an innovative derivatives that provides "
" for advanced traders. It allows buyers (taking the long side) to gain the Gamma exposure of an underlying asset and sellers (taking the short side) to earn funding fees by providing that exposure."

"The primary goal of Gamma Swap is to offer pure, constant Gamma exposure, making it extremely convenient for options traders to hedge their positions or liquidity providers to hedge against impermanent loss. Traders can check the Gamma value of their portfolio and then use the PNL simulator calculator to determine the amount of Gamma they want to adjust. This effectively hedges their portfolio's Gamma exposure."

"For the sellers on Gamma Swap, they can earn substantial funding payments by providing Gamma. This can be a profitable strategy for traders who are willing to take on the risk associated with providing Gamma to the market."
"The PNL (Profit and Loss) curve of a Gamma Swap is a parabola (ignoring slippage), with the equation PNL = (x - x"
", where x is the index price, and x"

" is the entry price (defaulted to the index price at the time of opening the position). This means that at any given time, the PNL (excluding fees and slippage) will be positive, and the greater the deviation of the price from the entry price, the higher the PNL will be."

"The unit for BTC Gamma Swap is set to one-thousandth (mBTC) because a single BTC's Gamma exposure can be too large for most people. However, for ETH, the natural unit is still used for Gamma Swap trading."
